</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uadonhiram.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adonhiram</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#333333>(8/10/02 6:24:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=882.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Boots of Bladecalling, BOIII pants</span><hr size=1> Thurgadin quest parts can be done solo at 58+. The occasional Lieutenant at bank in Kael drops (maybe 1/4 or 1/5 I camped Kael for weeks and got EVERY silk part but legs and robe, he bad luck, legs and robe are rarer than other parts, but can drop there) quest parts.<br>
<br>
Xp is awful, mobs hit super hard for their level (Lts are so 47+), you need your pet heal (chain casting against giants is a bit tricky as they have very long melee range and pathing in tunnel to bank is strange, you get hit by a giant who looks like 50 feet away), and a lot of patience. <br>
<br>
Just time the green roamer who comes from the Wakening side as he WILL aggro whatever id your level. And if Weng (forgot exact name) starts to leave bank area, finish your engaged giant quickly, as Krack is indifferent but will assist if a giant is attacked.<br>
<br>
All in all it is rather boring, but you learn how to pull in a medium dangerous train potent area, you will get 1 or 2 quest parts per day you can sell for MQ (between 1 and 2k for common ones, 5 to 7k for good ones like plate helm, and for the super lucky 20k for chest parts), and you are occasionnally grabbed to a spontaneous Arena raid.<br>
<br>
Bind yourself just at EW zone, because you will have to gate from time to time. Trains from EW are frequent (dropped invisibility etc etc). And sometimes you will aggro Captain Bvellos (don't try to solo him :-), as he roams now between bank and arena : sometimes you pull a watchman, and Bvellos - you could not see yet - was already too close on his roaming path and might assist. But the pathing gives you time to gate in that situation as the giants follow a square winkle isntead of charging you directly. So send pet to gain the some vital seconds, and hit your gate button.<br>
<br>
The placeholders are Watchmen (light blue to 59/60), a bit harder are the Sergeants (blue), and much harder but still soloable, the Lieutenants who can drop quest parts. Attention, Lieutenant Bvellos is a normal Lieutenant, Captain Bvellos is the big ass mob you must beware off.<br>
<br>
Use earth pet as root is required, because of the high hps, you have to nuke a lot and might draw aggro. On a watchman, you will need typically 1 pet heal and 3 nukes (Seukor or SoFB if you are 59+). On a Lieutenant, if not chain casting -but again giant's melee range plus pathing make chain casting a bit tricky-, you need between 4 mana bubs and a whole mana bar plus 1/2 charges of a rod.<br>
<br>
For Sergeants and Lieutenants, it is not a bad idea to use Wrath of Elements and/or Elemental Maelstroem, as you need fast damage, they hit so hard, he he...<br>
<br>
Be prepared to camp for long ... I did this a couple of weeks and got every silk part except the two I was looking for -Murphy's Law-, and take a break of Kael I am a bit saturated for now with this city....<br>
<br>
Keep the helmets and toes. 4 helmets to Chamberlain Krysstoff in Thurgadin will give you +faction with Coldain and Dain Frostreaver IV (8th shwal). 1 helmet and 1 toe (frost or storm giant) given to the entrance guards in Skyshrine give +faction with CoV and Yelinak.<br>
<br>
May the Silk be with You, Luke ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uanduransaryrn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anduran Saryrn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 12:54:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=882.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Boots</span><hr size=1> I have boots of bladecalling, and white dragonscale boots, it's pretty hard to say which is &quot;best&quot;.  For the purposese of soloing, then sure, the boots of bladecalling own, but when you're on raids, you're not going to be nuking a whole lot, you'll be mod rodding down to an inch of your life and getting chealed / torpored back to drop rods. In short... Boots of Bladecalling for solo, WDSB for raids =)<br>
<br>
-Anduran<br>
